The experiment `bow_opt_20260514_180714_run_04` using a Bag of Words (BoW) architecture with TF-IDF vectorization achieved a respectable F1 score of 0.7188 and an accuracy of 0.775, indicating that the model performed reasonably well on the validation set. The best threshold for classification was found to be 0.47, which suggests that this value effectively balanced precision and recall in the context of the dataset.

